    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 996-generation Carrera 2, featuring the 3.4L naturally aspirated flat-six mated to a crisp 6-speed longitudinal manual transaxle. This example remains mechanically robust, with the critical IMS bearing retrofit already completed and a fresh rear main seal. The suspension geometry is dialed in with Bilstein B8 dampers and M030-spec sway bars, ensuring neutral handling and minimized body roll through the apex. Braking is handled by four-piston monoblock calipers over vented rotors, showing excellent bite with no fade. While the finish shows minor road patina consistent with a driver\u2019s car, the drivetrain is tight, with no bore scoring and a linear power band all the way to the 7,200 RPM redline.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
